Rabies vaccination, boosters 980826195740
[1
Date: Thu, 27 Aug 1998 08:30:27 -0300
From: Wlamir Moura <wlamir@alpha.incqs.fiocruz.br>

It's my opinion that even [though being less immunogenic than modern
vaccines, F-P is a good vaccine and allowed the control of urban rabies
(animal and human) in Rio de Janeiro city and all Brazilian cities that
developed serious work in the massive animal single day vaccination.
There's no doubt that the modern vaccines are safer than it but no vaccine
failure has been reported in Brazil using F-D in the last years.
Researchers have shown that mice immunized with Flury HEP showed minimal
protection against Duvenhage and Mokola viruses, the only two known human
pathogens rabies-related viruses.
RNP is the antigen that gives the Lyssavirus group-specific antigenic cross
reactivity and even been shown that animal immunized with RNP can protect
against challenge, it's well known that neutralizing Ab are induced by the
glycoprotein (apparently responsible for the serotype determination of
Lyssavirus).
--
Wlamir Moura
Veterinary
Responsible for Rabies Vaccine Quality Control
FIOCRUZ - INCQS
Brazil
e-mail: wlamir@alpha.incqs.fiocruz.br
